race.comment: QUEEN ARIA (7) flew home to just miss fresh before stepping out to this trip last start and getting the job done comfortably. Pike hops back in the saddle now and she's expected to be better again now third-up into the campaign. Looks a nice mare on the way up and she can get the job done again. EXCELINDEED (3) was off a long break first-up but still jumped an odds-on chance when disappointing at Bunbury. He'll be better for that run and looks well suited out to this trip now. Brad Parnham replaces the apprentice hoop and a better showing is on the cards. BUNDABERG (8) was gunned down late by QUEEN ARIA last start but it is worth noting that he jumped an odds-on chance ahead of her there. Third-up now and he meets QUEEN ARIA slightly better at the weights. Can turn the tables. GIRLS ON FIRE (5) missed as favourite on resumption and now gets Chris Parnham and the blinkers on first time. Keep safe. SNIPPY SEAN (4) is better than we saw last start and can bounce back.
